webpackJsonp([64712532345142],{1056:function(A,e){A.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"Psyked: James' Web Development website",author:"James Ford"}},markdownRemark:{id:"/Users/James/Repositories/portfolio-2018/src/posts/alternativa3d-more-3d-goodness-from-the-flash-player/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>3D Flash engines seem to be popping up everywhere at the moment.  [Although I wouldn\'t call that a bad thing] - Each one tends to take a different approach, do a different demo to distinguish themselves.  Take this for example, a very impressive looking offering from Alternativa3D;</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/alternativa-f1640e20cb5b54841ab71fb2af9c1dc8-e8574.jpg"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 500px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 55.99999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="alternativa"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/alternativa-f1640e20cb5b54841ab71fb2af9c1dc8-e8574.jpg"\n        srcset="/static/alternativa-f1640e20cb5b54841ab71fb2af9c1dc8-c94d9.jpg 158w,\n/static/alternativa-f1640e20cb5b54841ab71fb2af9c1dc8-9885b.jpg 315w,\n/static/alternativa-f1640e20cb5b54841ab71fb2af9c1dc8-e8574.jpg 500w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Papervision might have a lot of features and a large fan-base, but I have yet to see such a visually impressive demo [as this one].  And they\'ve already sorted the first-person movement and collision detection.  It\'s also very cool that the demo seems to \'quickstart\' - loading low-res textures to get you going as soon as possible, and streaming in higher res. ones while you play.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/texturing-fb3292c2211486679f8484f6d7b71f8d-e8574.jpg"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 500px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 55.99999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="texturing"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/texturing-fb3292c2211486679f8484f6d7b71f8d-e8574.jpg"\n        srcset="/static/texturing-fb3292c2211486679f8484f6d7b71f8d-c94d9.jpg 158w,\n/static/texturing-fb3292c2211486679f8484f6d7b71f8d-9885b.jpg 315w,\n/static/texturing-fb3292c2211486679f8484f6d7b71f8d-e8574.jpg 500w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Progressive textures - how cool is that? (above)</p>\n<p>Of course, there\'s visual trickery going on here - the fantastic visuals are more down to excellent textures, rather than dynamic lighting or raytracing.  But that doesn\'t mean that the Alternativa3D team doesn\'t have that on their \'to-do\' list...</p>\n<p>So, what are you waiting for?  Go check it out at <a href="http://blog.alternativaplatform.com/en/" title="Open link in a new window">alternativaplatform.com</a>.</p>',frontmatter:{title:"Alternativa3D - More 3D goodness from the Flash Player",date:"May 03, 2008",tags:["external-links","flash","papervision"],url:null,image:null,description:null}}},pathContext:{prev:{frontmatter:{path:"/blog/open-screen-madness/",tags:["flash","flex","adobe","open-source"],title:"Open Screen madness?",date:"2008-05-01T23:48:57.000Z"}},next:{frontmatter:{path:"/blog/essential-actionscript-3-classes-1/",tags:["actionscript","external-links"],title:"Essential ActionScript 3 Classes #1",date:"2008-05-09T08:30:48.000Z"}}}}}});
